  "response_text": "A healthy way to season a chicken breast is to use a combination of fresh herbs, citrus, and spices. Here’s a simple recipe:\n\n### Lemon Herb Marinade\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon dried oregano (or 1 tablespoon fresh oregano, chopped)\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme (or 1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, minced garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper.\n2. Place the chicken breast in a resealable plastic bag or a shallow dish and pour the marinade over it. Make sure the chicken is well-coated.\n3. Marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes (up to 2 hours for more flavor).\n4. Grill, bake, or pan-sear the chicken breast until fully cooked.\n\nThis marinade not only adds flavor but also keeps the chicken moist and tender. Enjoy!",
